events.name: Front End TL;DR February 2016
events.description:
Address: 9th floor, South Beach Tower, 38 Beach Road, Singapore 189767

Have you ever come across something new in front end, had the browser tab open for weeks, but never found time to research it? Use this event as an excuse to dig a little deeper.

Front End TL;DR is a learning event where everyone participates. Helps to bring a laptop.

Join to level-up your front-end knowledge, meet other front-end developers, or learn how the engineers at the venue host ship code.

7:00pm — Arrival, seating, food & drinks 
7:15pm — Intro talk by the host 
7:30pm — R&D: random team assignment, choose a topic, learn something new 
9:00pm — Q&A: share what your team learned 
9:30–10:00pm — The end.

There should be guest wifi. Food & drinks sometimes provided (ymmv).

Every third Monday of the month. Different venue each time.

More info: http://feds.strikingly.com/
events.location: Expedia Singapore - 9F, South Beach Tower, 38 Beach Road, Singapore 189767

events.name: Welcome!
events.description:
Its exciting to have a Linux kernel meetup group in Singapore, and I am organizing our first meetup. This will be a very informal techno socializing event to know interests in the group. Light snacks will be arranged. Event date and location is as above. 


Interested participants please register at            http://goo.gl/forms/xfjsJkli8x 


There is no planned talks, however if any of the participant is keen in conducting a workshop or short  talk  please email me at the id below. If there is common interest on a topic could discuss on that as well. The meetup is free of cost. Thanks! See you soon. anajain.sg At gmail.com
